    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge and open the packet to let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-chicken-ciabatta-with-herby-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and drizzle with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and season with your <strong>dried oregano </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25 min or until golden and crisp \u2013 these are your <strong>herby roast potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-chicken-ciabatta-with-herby-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken </strong>to a plate with your<strong> cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-chicken-ciabatta-with-herby-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!), <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-chicken-ciabatta-with-herby-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>spiced chicken </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden, then add a couple of splashes of <strong>water</strong> to the pan and cover with a lid</p><p>Cook for a further 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-chicken-ciabatta-with-herby-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> to a separate baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 5 min or until it is hot and toasted</p><p>Carefully slice in half before serving</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-chicken-ciabatta-with-herby-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper and shred roughly</p><p>Slice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into rounds</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spiced-chicken-ciabatta-with-herby-roast-sweet-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To assemble, fill the <strong>warmed ciabatta </strong>with the <strong>spiced chicken</strong>, <strong>tomato rounds </strong>and<strong> </strong>a<strong> </strong>dollop of<strong> garlic mayo</strong> with a handful of <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>spiced chicken sandwich</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>herby roast</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to the side with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>shredded</strong> <strong>lettuce</strong> and drizzle over the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>garlic mayo</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
